DESIGN MAP (scoped 2026-07-02, released to open for a focused window; cross-cutting, needs full budget). Reverse-engineered the seam; no code written this window (nothing to revert).

THE GAP: Evidence.VerificationRerunner.run_attempt/4 (verification_rerunner.ex:137-139) defaults :runner to a NO-OP fn returning %{exit_code: 0, stdout: ""} -- production verification executes NOTHING. Gate stage test_execution.ex:56-58 only passes a :runner if context carries :verification_runner|:runner, else [] -> no-op. So production gate "reruns" are vacuous unless a runner is threaded.

RUNNER CONTRACT: a fn(command_spec) -> %{exit_code, stdout, stderr}. Eval/pytest already provide one: ToolchainRunner.runner/2 (toolchain_runner.ex:60) returns fn command -> exec(backend, ws, command, opts) end. First-light/eval tests thread it via :runner, so they are UNAFFECTED by a default change.

BUILD (the generic runner): new module (e.g. Conveyor.Verification.CommandRunner) exposing runner(workspace_path, policy, opts) -> fn command_spec -> ... end that:
1. builds a Policy.NormalizedCommand from the spec (argv -> executable+argv, cwd, network, env_allowlist, timeout_ms);
2. calls ToolExecutor.execute!(cmd, policy, opts) -- the SOLE trusted pre-exec policy path (Engine.evaluate! -> :blocked refused -> satisfies "disallowed command refused");
3. on :allowed reads execution.stdout/exit_code from the Runner.Result;
4. for result_format junit|json reads the DECLARED ARTIFACT FILE from a PER-RUN TEMP path (kills the .conveyor_eval_junit.xml hardcode at toolchain_runner.ex:48) and returns it as the output the existing run_attempt hands to TestResultAdapter.parse!; stdout format uses stdout directly;
5. fail-honest: :blocked or missing artifact -> a failure result with reason, never silent pass (mirror the M4 empty-acceptance-suite-fails rule).
Inject the low-level exec (default &Sandbox.Runner.exec/1) so unit tests run the command_spec matrix (junit/stdout/json/nonzero/missing-artifact) at $0.

ROUTE: thread the generic runner into the PRODUCTION gate context so test_execution uses it by default -- build site is SerialDriver's gate_context/run_gate (needs workspace_path + resolved Policy; both already in the run context). Keep pytest as the python-profile SPECIALIZATION invoked through the same seam (ToolchainRunner.exec becomes the venv/uv env-prep behind the profile). Env prep stays profile business (python venv, elixir mix deps.get, js npm ci) -- OUT of the generic runner.

TESTS: unit matrix (formats x exit codes x missing artifact, injected exec); sample-python first_light e2e unchanged (regression -- it passes its own runner so only the DEFAULT changes); design-laws grep: no direct pytest/System.cmd/ToolchainRunner invocation outside the seam (scope note lists all sites: verify station, acceptance-calibration station, MutantGauntlet, gate TestExecution rerun).
